# SDLC Setup & Quality Gates - Freshworks App Monorepo

Comprehensive checklist for managing the Software Development Life Cycle in a Freshworks CRM app environment. Use this when spinning up new apps, services, or major features.

**Justification:** Structured SDLC prevents technical debt, ensures quality, and reduces production incidents in enterprise CRM integrations.

## SDLC Phases Overview

1. **Plan & Spec** → Define goals, users, scope, success criteria, risks
2. **Design** → Architecture, data models, APIs, UI flows, test strategy
3. **Implement** → Code + tests + configs (with continuous quality gates)
4. **Verify** → Automated + manual testing, QA
5. **Release** → Deploy, migrate, feature toggles
6. **Operate** → Monitor, alert, incident response
7. **Improve** → Learnings, backlog, iteration

## SDLC Checklist - Order of Operations

Use this checklist for new apps/services or major features. Each phase builds on the previous.

### 🚀 Phase 1: Project Initialization & Planning

**Repository & Workspace Setup**
- [ ] Create repository with main branch protection rules
- [ ] Initialize pnpm workspace (monorepo structure)
- [ ] Set up Nx workspace configuration
- [ ] Add appropriate Nx tags for dependency constraints

**Documentation & Governance**
- [ ] Choose license (MIT for open-source components)
- [ ] Create README.md with setup instructions
- [ ] Add CONTRIBUTING.md guidelines
- [ ] Configure CODEOWNERS for domain reviewers
- [ ] Document success criteria and acceptance tests

### 🛡️ Phase 2: Quality Gates & Development Standards

**Code Quality Tools**
- [ ] Add Prettier formatter with consistent rules
- [ ] Configure ESLint with strict TypeScript rules
- [ ] Enable TypeScript strict mode (noImplicitAny, etc.)
- [ ] Add Husky pre-commit hooks + lint-staged
- [ ] Configure .editorconfig for consistent formatting

**Testing Framework Setup**
- [ ] Add Vitest for unit tests (preferred for new projects)
- [ ] Configure Jest for existing packages (backward compatibility)
- [ ] Set up test coverage thresholds (80% global, 70% per-file)
- [ ] Add mutation testing (Stryker) for critical paths
- [ ] Create smoke test for basic functionality

### 🔧 Phase 3: Infrastructure & Configuration

**Environment Management**
- [ ] Define environments: dev, staging, prod (+ PR previews)
- [ ] Create .env.example with all required variables
- [ ] Set up secret management (GitHub Secrets, SSM, Doppler)
- [ ] Implement 12-factor config (env vars, no secrets in code)
- [ ] Add runtime config validation (fail fast on boot)

**CI/CD Pipeline**
- [ ] Configure GitHub Actions with Nx affected commands
- [ ] Set up pnpm store caching for faster builds
- [ ] Implement PR pipeline: install → typecheck → lint → test → build
- [ ] Add accessibility checks (a11y) for UI components
- [ ] Configure SBOM generation and dependency scanning
- [ ] Ensure fast feedback (<10 min for basic checks)

### 🧪 Phase 4: Testing Strategy Implementation

**Unit Testing (White-box)**
- [ ] Write unit tests for all new functions and classes
- [ ] Use Vitest with TypeScript support
- [ ] Mock external dependencies (APIs, databases)
- [ ] Achieve coverage thresholds (80% global, 70% per-file)
- [ ] Add mutation testing for critical business logic

**Integration Testing**
- [ ] Test module/service interactions
- [ ] Add contract tests for API boundaries
- [ ] Mock external services (Freshsales, ElevenLabs, Telnyx)
- [ ] Test database operations with test containers
- [ ] Verify authentication and authorization flows

**End-to-End Testing**
- [ ] Implement smoke tests (basic functionality verification)
- [ ] Add sanity tests for critical user journeys
- [ ] Create regression tests for existing features
- [ ] Set up Playwright for UI component testing
- [ ] Automate webhook service integration tests

### 🚀 Phase 5: Deployment & Release

**Preview & Staging**
- [ ] Set up ephemeral preview deployments per PR
- [ ] Configure staging environment for main branch merges
- [ ] Implement feature flags for gradual rollouts
- [ ] Add database migration scripts (if needed)
- [ ] Configure blue-green deployment strategy

**Production Release**
- [ ] Set up manual approval gates for production
- [ ] Implement canary deployments for high-risk changes
- [ ] Add automated rollback procedures
- [ ] Configure health checks and monitoring
- [ ] Set up alerting for production incidents

### 📊 Phase 6: Observability & Operations

**Logging & Monitoring**
- [ ] Implement structured JSON logging
- [ ] Add OpenTelemetry traces and metrics
- [ ] Configure health endpoints (/healthz, /ready)
- [ ] Set up error tracking (Sentry) with context
- [ ] Create dashboards for key SLIs/SLOs

**Security & Compliance**
- [ ] Enable dependency vulnerability scanning
- [ ] Configure secret scanning in CI
- [ ] Set up least-privilege IAM roles
- [ ] Implement encryption at rest and in transit
- [ ] Add HIPAA compliance mode for PHI modules

**Operational Readiness**
- [ ] Document runbook (local dev, deploy, rollback)
- [ ] Set up on-call rotation and alerting
- [ ] Create incident response procedures
- [ ] Add post-deployment smoke tests
- [ ] Configure backup and disaster recovery

### 📚 Phase 7: Documentation & Knowledge

**Technical Documentation**
- [ ] Create architecture diagrams (system, data flow)
- [ ] Document API contracts and schemas
- [ ] Write ADRs for architectural decisions
- [ ] Add inline code documentation
- [ ] Create troubleshooting guides

**Operational Documentation**
- [ ] Document deployment procedures
- [ ] Create monitoring and alerting runbooks
- [ ] Add security incident response guides
- [ ] Document backup and recovery procedures
- [ ] Create performance tuning guidelines

## Quality Gates by Phase

### Pre-commit (Automatic)
- [ ] Code formatting (Prettier)
- [ ] Linting (ESLint)
- [ ] Type checking (TypeScript)
- [ ] Unit tests pass

### Pre-merge (PR Review)
- [ ] All pre-commit checks pass
- [ ] Code review by domain experts
- [ ] Integration tests pass
- [ ] Accessibility checks pass (for UI)
- [ ] Security scanning clean

### Pre-deploy (CI/CD)
- [ ] Full test suite passes
- [ ] Build artifacts generated
- [ ] SBOM and vulnerability scan complete
- [ ] Smoke tests pass in staging

### Post-deploy (Production)
- [ ] Health checks pass
- [ ] Monitoring alerts configured
- [ ] Rollback plan documented
- [ ] Incident response team notified

## Success Metrics

- **Development Velocity**: PR merge time < 24 hours
- **Code Quality**: 0 critical linting errors, 80%+ test coverage
- **Reliability**: 99.9% uptime, < 5 min incident response
- **Security**: 0 critical vulnerabilities in production
- **User Experience**: All accessibility standards met